snippet: Residents assessed the damage in four states and braced for more possible damage on Sunday after a warning of a “high-end, life-threatening event.”
abstract: Tornadoes are reported in Nebraska, Kansas and Oklahoma, and strong storms push through Iowa; no deaths or severe injuries are immediately reported; National Weather Service issues warning for residents from East Texas to the Great Lakes to prepare for dangerous weather.
lead_paragraph: Residents assessed the damage in four states and braced for more possible damage on Sunday after a warning of a “high-end, life-threatening event.”

headline.seo: Tornadoes and Storms Hit Iowa, Kansas, Nebraska, and Oklahoma
headline.main: Tornadoes and Storms Pepper the Plains
